  <prompt>
    Add unit tests for `NarrativeBullet` covering: sub-list rendering when `itemIds.length &gt; 1`; single-item bullets unchanged; sub-row link click invokes `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` with correct args; sub-row To-Do invokes `useInlineTodoCreate` with the specific underlying item; sub-row Dismiss vs aggregated Dismiss cascade behavior. Add a dark-mode visual regression check.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in React Testing Library + visual regression tooling + Fluent v9 dark-mode validation.</role>

  <goal>Comprehensive P2a test coverage; dark-mode parity asserted; all tests green.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per NFR-05 and ADR-021: tests must cover the new sub-list rendering + dark mode. The 4 sub-row behaviors (link, To-Do, sub-row Dismiss, aggregated cascade Dismiss) each get their own unit test.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/test/NarrativeBullet.test.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">NFR-05: test coverage for hoisted shared package.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Dark-mode parity asserted (no hard-coded colors regress).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/unit-test-structure.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/mocking-patterns.md</file>
