  <steps>
    <step order="1">Write `NarrativeBullet.test.tsx` with the following cases:</step>
    <step order="2">Case 1: `itemIds.length === 1` — no sub-list rendered.</step>
    <step order="3">Case 2: `itemIds.length &gt; 1` — sub-list with N rows rendered.</step>
    <step order="4">Case 3: sub-row link click invokes `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` with the underlying item's `regardingEntityType` + `regardingId` (FR-12).</step>
    <step order="5">Case 4: sub-row Add-to-To-Do invokes `useInlineTodoCreate` with the specific underlying item (FR-13).</step>
    <step order="6">Case 5: sub-row Dismiss invokes `markAsRead(item.id)` for that single id (FR-14).</step>
    <step order="7">Case 6: aggregated Dismiss invokes `markAsRead` for each id in `itemIds[]` (FR-14a cascade).</step>
    <step order="8">Case 7: dark-mode rendering — assert computed colors use semantic tokens (or visual regression snapshot in dark mode).</step>
    <step order="9">Run `npm test`; all green.</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 024 status from 🔲 to ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Run test suite.</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="test">src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/test/NarrativeBullet.test.tsx</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All 7 test cases exist and pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Dark-mode case asserts semantic-token usage (or snapshots).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The dark-mode test may use a JSDOM-friendly token lookup OR a Playwright snapshot — either works. Spec doesn't prescribe one.
